      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Screen design inherited most of its conventions from print without inheriting print's constraints. Understanding where those conventions came from — movable type, the compositing stick, the job case, the press sheet — illuminates why we still think in columns, why we still kern between letters, and why the grid feels natural even when everything else about the medium has changed.",
